Wildfires have erupted around the world; the most devastating in Turkey. 😢 Italy, USA, Spain, France, Cyprus, Finland, Lebanon, Canada & Greece have also had terrible fires! There has been severe flooding in Germany, China, Italy, Belgium & Netherlands. Hail bigger than tennis balls has rained down in northern Italy, and it’s even snowed in Brazil!
The second largest river in South America, Paraná River, is currently suffering from a severe drought, and we’ve seen tornadoes in Czechia. 🙏🏽 🌎 😞

Please tag your friends, share this on your stories!

I’ve had countless messages my from wonderful Turkish followers today, asking to share this. To all of you, my thoughts are with you, your family and your friends. 🙏🏽 via @earthfocus

node.text:
Stags - and other deer - forcibly expel air through their nostrils like a greatly magnified sneeze. The deer blows when it detects danger at a distance or is agitated. These blows are drawn-out “whooshes” repeated several times. Snorts are single, very short, explosive sounds and are often given to alarm call as the deer turns to run.
Incredible video by Priscilla Mordecai Earhart
